  .w-100.h-gr.text-white(style="background:url(/assets/img/about-bg.jpg) center center fixed no-repeat;background-size:cover"): .vertical-center: .w-100.text-center
    img.mb-4(src="/assets/img/icon.svg",style="width:3em;opacity:.1;margin-top:-1em")
    h1 Hacks/Hackers Taipei
    p 關於我們
  .typeset.heading-contrast: .p-4.w-768.mx-auto.rwd
    .py-4
      h2 什麼是 Hacks/Hackers？
      p #[a(href="http://hackshackers.com/") Hacks/Hackers]（簡稱H/H） 是由美國西北大學新聞學院教授 Rich Gordon、Storify 創辦人Burt Herman、前紐約時報互動新聞主編 Aron Pilhofer 從2009年開始逐漸發展出的非營利新聞社群，鼓勵記者編輯（Hacks）和程式設計師（Hackers）相互學習、合作，一起想像新聞的未來。
      p 目前全球已有 35 個國家、75 個城市建立 Hacks/Hackers 分支（chapter），其他城市的活動可以看 #[a(href="http://www.meetup.com/hacks-hackers-nyc/?https=off") 這裡] 、 #[a(href="https://github.com/HacksHackersAfrica/wiki/wiki/Hacks-Hackers-Charter") 這裡] 以及 #[a(href="http://hackshackers.com/chapters/") 這裡] 。
    .py-4
      h2 HacksHackers Taipei是什麼？
      p 繼香港、東京、北京成立 Hacks/Hackers 分支之後，2016年10月由一群關心新聞x科技發展的朋友在台北成立 Hacks/Hackers 在亞洲的第四站。
    .py-4
      h2 我們要做什麼？
      p 我們希望能促進交流、刺激想法，會不定期舉辦線下聚會，透過教學工作坊、案例分享、黑客松等形式鼓勵參與者交換技術和想法。如果你有任何點子和建議，歡迎email給我們：hackshackerstaipei[at]gmail.com
    .py-4
      h2 怎麼追蹤我們？
      p 您可以透過以下管道追蹤我們的訊息：
      ul
        li: a(href="https://hackshackers.taipei/") Hacks/Hackers Taipei 官方網站 ( https://hackshackers.taipei )
        li: a(href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/868771643258752/") 臉書社團
        li: a(href="https://twitter.com/hackshackerstpe") Twitter 帳號
        li: a(href="https://github.com/hackshackerstaipei/") Github
        li: a(href="https://hhtpe.slack.com/") Slack 線上聊天室
      p  或者訂閱我們的 #[a(href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=4f9ctnr08nmq02hfs7vbu8l9f0%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=Asia/Taipei") Google Calendar] 追蹤最新活動。

    .p-4
    .py-4
      h2 What is Hacks/Hackers?
      p The roots of Hacks/Hackers were planted in 2009, co-founded by Aron Pilhofer of The New York Times, Rich Gordon from Northwestern University’s Medill School of Journalism, Burt Herman, a former AP foreign correspondent fresh from a Knight journalism fellowship at Stanford University. Hacks/Hackers grew from an initial chapter in the Bay Area in late 2009 to flourishing chapters in New York, Boston, Austin and other cities during 2010. Hacks/Hackers has also gone international, with chapters launching in Latin America, Europe, Australia and Asia.
      p Hacks/Hackers’ mission is to create a network of journalists (“hacks”) and technologists (“hackers”) who rethink the future of news and information.
    .py-4
      h2 What is Hacks/Hackers Taipei?
      p Founded in Oct 2016 by a group of friends, who cares about what technology can do for journalism and vice versa. Abide by the #[a(href="https://github.com/HacksHackersAfrica/wiki/wiki/Hacks-Hackers-Charter") Hacks/Hackers Chapter].
    .py-4
      h2 What do we do?
      p Our mission is to spread knowledge, information and ideas. Activities include workshops, talks, hackathons and demo days. If you have any ideas, please email us at hackshackerstaipei[at]gmail.com.
    .py-4
      h2 How to keep connected?
      p You can find us on:
      ul
        li: a(href="https://hackshackers.taipei/") Hacks/Hackers Taipei Official Website ( https://hackshackers.taipei )
        li: a(href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/868771643258752/") Facebook Group
        li: a(href="https://twitter.com/hackshackerstpe") Twitter Account
        li: a(href="https://github.com/hackshackerstaipei/") Github
        li: a(href="https://hhtpe.slack.com/") Slack
      p or subscribe our #[a(href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=4f9ctnr08nmq02hfs7vbu8l9f0%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=Asia/Taipei") Google Calendar] events.

